parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS brake system can cause the brakes to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal or lever becomes hard or frozen
the brakes do not respond or engage
the brakes vibrate or pulse
the brake fluid leaks or is low
the ABS light illuminates on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal or lever becomes hard or frozen
the brakes do not respond or engage
the brake fluid leaks or is low
the master cylinder needs to be rebuilt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brakes to malfunction or fail, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal or lever becomes hard or frozen
the brakes do not respond or engage
the brake fluid leaks or is low
the brake system needs to be bled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the compensator can cause loose metal pieces to obstruct the drive chain and sprocket, leading to a sudden loss of control and potentially catastrophic accidents.
symptoms: Rattling noise in the primary case area
loose metal pieces found in the primary case
potential for sudden loss of control or accident.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the throttle body wiring connector can cause the bike to suddenly shut down or lose power, leading to a loss of control and potentially dangerous situations.
symptoms: Sudden loss of throttle response
bike goes into limp mode
sudden shutdown of the bike
throttling issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Harley Davidson's flawed design of the compensator and throttle body wiring connector can lead to dangerous situations and potentially catastrophic accidents.
symptoms: Various symptoms related to compensator failure and throttle body wiring connector failure
including rattling noise
loose metal pieces
sudden loss of throttle response
and bike shutdown.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Throttle Control Actuator (TCA) Terminal Pin Corrosion/Fretting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion or fretting of the terminal pins on the Throttle Control Actuator (TCA) can cause the vehicle to shut down into limp mode, reducing speed in less than 5 seconds, which can lead to accidents or near-misses, especially when traveling at high speeds or in group rides.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down into limp mode
reducing speed in less than 5 seconds
trouble codes P1511 and/or P2135 are stored
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power.
